  <!-- ============================================================= -->
  <!-- GOVERNANCE                                                    -->
  <!-- ============================================================= -->
  <governance>
    <issue id="ISS-HIERARCHICAL" status="review" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        Should the behavior section eventually support hierarchical or parallel
        (AND) states beyond the current flat model?
      </statement>
      <notes>Deferred in RFC-0002 as a possible future RFC to preserve LLM legibility.</notes>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-GUARD-LANG" status="review" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        Should transition guards adopt a small structured expression language
        instead of free text?
      </statement>
      <notes>Open question in RFC-0002; free text risks ambiguity (RISK-AMBIGUITY).</notes>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-INTERFACES-NA" status="approved" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        The interfaces section is intentionally omitted from this self-spec:
        RQML is a format, not a running service with APIs or events.
      </statement>
      <notes>Resolved: omission is correct and schema-valid (interfaces is optional).</notes>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-IMPL-TRACE" status="review" owner="STK-TOOLBUILDERS">
      <statement>
        implements trace edges (E-IMPL-*) now link the built schema, core, cli,
        and mcp packages to their requirements, and verifiedBy edges (E-VER-*)
        link requirements to the executable test files. The agent-loop build of
        2026-06-09 (PKG-LOOP) closed the earlier gaps: REQ-MCP-TOOLS shipped its
        skeleton tool, and REQ-SM-INITIAL, REQ-SM-FINAL, and REQ-TRANSITION-REFS
        are now enforced in code by checkIntegrity (REQ-CORE-SM-INTEGRITY).
        Still intentionally unlinked: REQ-ENFORCE-CERTIFIED (append-only audit
        trail not yet implemented), REQ-CLI-SPEED (latency target not yet
        benchmarked), REQ-ENFORCE-AUTHOR-SPLIT (process property), and the
        format-property and process requirements with no single code artifact
        (REQ-LLM-READ, REQ-DIFF, REQ-HUMAN, REQ-VALIDATABLE, REQ-SPEC-FIRST,
        REQ-NORMATIVE-KEYWORDS).
      </statement>
      <notes>
        Loop edges from 2026-06-09 onward are recorded with rqml link, which
        also captures the drift baseline (.rqml/baseline.json); rqml check now
        detects changed artifacts, not just missing ones.
      </notes>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-PLUGIN-SCOPE" status="approved" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        The Claude Code plugin and hooks that consume these primitives are
        specified in a separate integration repository, not here. This document
        specifies only the in-repo toolchain that provides the primitives.
      </statement>
      <notes>Keeps the self-spec focused on the rqml monorepo.</notes>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-MCP-PACKAGE" status="approved" owner="STK-TOOLBUILDERS">
      <statement>
        The MCP server is shipped as its own package (@rqml/mcp) rather than as a
        CLI subcommand.
      </statement>
      <notes>Resolved in favor of three packages: core, cli, mcp.</notes>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-LOOP-SCOPE" status="review" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        The agent-loop package (PKG-LOOP) is scoped to deterministic operations
        on the spec itself. Excluded by design: generation of target-language
        code or tests from entities, criteria, or interfaces (the model's job
        per DEC-DETERMINISTIC-CHECK); symbol- or AST-level drift resolution
        (file-granularity hashes suffice); and cross-document locator
        resolution, deferred until a multi-document consumer exists.
      </statement>
      <notes>Boundary recorded 2026-06-09 to keep the toolchain lightweight.</notes>
    </issue>
    <issue id="ISS-PROCESS-GATE" status="review" owner="STK-MAINTAINER">
      <statement>
        Whether the deterministic check gate should become ADR- and plan-aware —
        e.g. flagging an approved ADR-worthy decision with no .rqml/adr/ file, or
        a missing .rqml/plan.md for multi-stage work. Deferred (DEC-FIVE-STAGE):
        the gate stays validation+coverage+drift so no model enters the verdict
        path and the documented exit-code contract is unchanged; Design and Plan
        adherence is guided by agent integrations for now. Revisit once the
        five-stage process has field experience across the plugins.
      </statement>
      <notes>Recorded 2026-06-13 alongside adoption of the five-stage process.</notes>
    </issue>
    <approval id="APR-MAINTAINER" role="RQML Maintainer" status="review">
      <description>Maintainer sign-off on the RQML self-specification.</description>
    </approval>
  </governance>

</rqml>
